Reading in the data and setting the control treatment as baseline level

# Read in data
final_data <- read_excel("C:/Users/Win10/Desktop/UCT/Honours Project Gracilaria/Data/Statistical_Analyses_R/Raw_data_complete.xlsx")


# Set the Control treatment as the reference/baseline level
final_data$Treatment <- as.factor(final_data$Treatment)
final_data$Treatment <- relevel(final_data$Treatment, ref = "Control")

Gracilaria gracilis

Length

Filtering the data and calculating averages

# Filter data by species and length
gg_length <- final_data %>%
  filter(Measurement_Type == "Length", Species == "Gracilaria gracilis" )
  
# Calculate mean, SD and SE
gg_avg_length <- gg_length %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Tank_No,Week) %>%
  summarise(Average = mean(Value,na.rm = TRUE), SD = sd(Value), N = n(),
SE = SD / sqrt(N), Date = max(Date),.groups = "drop") %>% 
  ungroup() 

# Average treatment length per week
gg_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment <- gg_avg_length  %>%
  group_by( Week,Treatment) %>%
  summarise(
    Average = mean(Average,na.rm = TRUE), N = n(),
    SD = mean(SD,na.rm = TRUE), SE = mean(SE,na.rm = TRUE),
    Date = max(Date), .groups = "drop")

Testing ANOVA assumptions, creating models and running post hoc test

# Shapiro-Wilk normality test to test normality of gg avg length per treatment per week
shapiro.test(gg_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment$Average) # normality assumption met
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  gg_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment$Average
## W = 0.88059, p-value = 0.08919
# Levene's Test to check for homogeneity of treatments in gg avg length per treatment per week
leveneTest(gg_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment$Average, 
gg_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment$Treatment, center = mean ) # assumption of equal variances met
## Levene's Test for Homogeneity of Variance (center = mean)
##       Df F value Pr(>F)
## group  2  1.0912 0.3764
##        9
# Model of average length per treatment per week
mGAL <-  aov(Average ~ Treatment + Week, data = gg_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment)
summary(mGAL)

Figures

Specific Growth Rate (SGR) for Length

#  Calculate specific growth rate (SGR) of length of both species of seaweed
gg_avg_length$Date <- as.Date(gg_avg_length$Date) # proper format

gg_rgr_length <- gg_avg_length %>%
arrange(Tank_No) %>% 
group_by(Tank_No,Treatment) %>%
  mutate(Delta_Time = as.numeric((Date) - lag(Date)),
  RGR_Length = (log(Average) - lag(log(Average))) / Delta_Time,
  Tot_RGR = (Average[Week == 3]-Average[Week == 0])/as.numeric(max(Date)-min(Date)), 
  RGR_Per =  ((log(Average) - lag(log(Average))) / Delta_Time)*100)

 rgr_weekly_sd <- gg_rgr_length %>%
  group_by(Week,Treatment) %>%
  mutate(
    SD_RGR_Per = sd(RGR_Per, na.rm = TRUE),
    N = sum(!is.na(RGR_Per)), SE_RGR_Per = SD_RGR_Per / sqrt(N)) %>%
   ungroup()

gg_avg_rgr_length <- rgr_weekly_sd %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Week) %>%
  summarise(
  RGR_Length = mean(RGR_Length,na.rm = TRUE), N = n(),
  Tot_RGR = mean(Tot_RGR, na.rm = TRUE),
  RGR_Per = mean(RGR_Per, na.rm = TRUE),
  RGR_Per_SD = mean(SD_RGR_Per, na.rm = TRUE),
  RGR_Per_SE = mean(SE_RGR_Per),
  Date = max(Date), .groups = "drop") %>%
ungroup()

Testing ANOVA Assumptions, modelling and post hoc test

# Shapiro-Wilk normality test 
shapiro.test(gl_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment$Average) # normality assumption not met
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  gl_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment$Average
## W = 0.8447, p-value = 0.0316
# Levene's Test to check for homogeneity of treatments 
leveneTest(Average ~ Treatment, center = mean, data = gl_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment) # equal variances assumption not met
## Levene's Test for Homogeneity of Variance (center = mean)
##       Df F value  Pr(>F)  
## group  2  5.2489 0.03084 *
##        9                  
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
# Use generalised least squares model instead of linear model
m_LAL <- gls(
  Average ~ Treatment + Week,
  weights = varIdent(form = ~1 | Treatment),  
  data = gl_avg_length_per_week_by_treatment
)
summary(m_LAL)

#  Calculate specific growth rate (SGR) of length of Gracilariopsis longissima
gl_avg_length$Date <- as.Date(gl_avg_length$Date) # proper format

gl_rgr_length <- gl_avg_length %>%
arrange(Tank_No) %>% 
group_by(Tank_No,Treatment) %>%
  mutate(Delta_Time = as.numeric((Date) - lag(Date)),
  RGR_Length = (log(Average) - lag(log(Average))) / Delta_Time,
  Tot_RGR = (Average[Week == 3]-Average[Week == 0])/as.numeric(max(Date)-min(Date)),
   RGR_Per = ((log(Average) - lag(log(Average))) / Delta_Time)*100)

rgr_weekly_sd <- gl_rgr_length %>%
  group_by(Week,Treatment) %>%
  mutate(
    RGR_Per_SD = sd(RGR_Per, na.rm = TRUE),
  N = sum(!is.na(RGR_Per)), 
  SE_RGR_Per = RGR_Per_SD / sqrt(N)) %>%
  ungroup()

    
gl_avg_rgr_length <- rgr_weekly_sd %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Week) %>%
  summarise(
  RGR_Length = mean(RGR_Length,na.rm = TRUE), N = n(),
  Tot_RGR = mean(Tot_RGR, na.rm = TRUE),
    RGR_Per = mean(RGR_Per, na.rm = TRUE),
    RGR_Per_SD = mean(RGR_Per_SD, na.rm = TRUE),
  RGR_Per_SE = mean(SE_RGR_Per, na.rm = TRUE),
  Date = max(Date), .groups = "drop") %>%
ungroup()

Combine Weight and Length DGRs in bar graph for Gracilaria gracilis

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

# Combine the two datasets, adding a column to distinguish length vs weight
gg_rgr_combined <- bind_rows(
  gg_avg_rgr_length %>% mutate(Type = "Length"),
  gg_avg_rgr_weight %>% mutate(Type = "Weight")
)


gg_rgr_combined_plot <- gg_rgr_combined %>%
  filter(Treatment %in% c(5, 10)) %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Type) %>%
  summarise(Mean_RGR_Per = mean(RGR_Per, na.rm = TRUE), 
            RGR_Per_SE = mean(RGR_Per_SE, na.rm = TRUE),.groups = "drop") %>%
  ungroup()

# Plot
ggplot(gg_rgr_combined_plot, aes(x = Treatment, y = Mean_RGR_Per, fill = Type)) +
  geom_col(position = position_dodge(width = 0.3), color = "black", width = 0.2) +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = Mean_RGR_Per, ymax = Mean_RGR_Per + RGR_Per_SE),
                width = 0.2, position = position_dodge(width = 0.3)) +
  scale_fill_grey(start = 1, end = 0) +
  geom_smooth(aes(group = Type), color = "black",method = "lm", se = FALSE, linetype = "solid") +
  labs(
    title = expression("Daily Growth Rate of " * italic("Gracilaria gracilis") * " by Treatment"),
    x = "Treatment",
    y = "DGR (%)",
    fill = "",
    color = ""
  ) +
  theme_classic(base_size = 14) +
  theme(
    axis.line = element_line(color = "black", size = 0.5),
    axis.ticks = element_line(color = "black"),
    legend.position = "top"
  )
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Bar graph of Final lengths and weights of Gracilariopsis longissima

gl_combined <- bind_rows(
  gl_avg_length %>% mutate(Type = "Length"),
  gl_avg_weight %>% mutate(Type = "Weight"))

gl_combined_plot <- gl_combined %>%
  filter(Treatment %in% c(5, 10), Week == "3") %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Type) %>%
  summarise(Net_Yield = mean(Average, na.rm = TRUE),
   SE = mean(SE, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop") %>%
  ungroup()


# plot

# Rescale length to match weight scale
# Find max values
max_weight <- max(gl_combined_plot$Net_Yield[gl_combined_plot$Type == "Weight"], na.rm = TRUE)
max_length <- max(gl_combined_plot$Net_Yield[gl_combined_plot$Type == "Length"], na.rm = TRUE)

scale_factor <- max_weight / max_length

gl_combined_plot <- gl_combined_plot %>%
  mutate(Net_Yield_scaled = ifelse(Type == "Length", Net_Yield * scale_factor, Net_Yield),
         SE_scaled = ifelse(Type == "Length", SE * scale_factor, SE))

ggplot(gl_combined_plot, aes(x = factor(Treatment), fill = Type)) +
  geom_col(aes(y = Net_Yield_scaled), 
           position = position_dodge(width = 0.4), 
           color = "black", width = 0.3) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = Net_Yield_scaled, ymax = Net_Yield_scaled + SE_scaled),
                width = 0.2, position = position_dodge(width = 0.4)) +
  scale_fill_grey(start = 1, end = 0) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    name = "Net yield (g)", 
    sec.axis = sec_axis(~ . / scale_factor, name = "Net yield (cm)")
  ) +
  labs(
    title = expression("Net yield of " * italic("Gracilariopsis longissima") * " by Treatment"),
    x = "Initial total length",
    fill = ""
  ) +
  theme_classic(base_size = 14) +
  theme(
    axis.line = element_line(color = "black", size = 0.5),
    axis.ticks = element_line(color = "black"),
    legend.position = "top"
  )
